title: AFL 2015: GWS v Geelong, Adelaide v Gold Coast, live coverage | The
text:
GWS can extend its stay inside the top eight with a victory over the struggling Geelong at StarTrack Oval to begin Saturday’s AFL action.
That match will coincide with Adelaide’s clash with Gold Coast at the Adelaide Oval, as the Crows hope to build on last weekend’s Showdown victory with another win.
FOR FULL LIVE HQ COVERAGE WITH SUPERCOACH SCORES CLICK ON THE GAME IN THE SCORE CENTRE ABOVE OR HERE IF YOU ARE ON A MOBILE DEVICE
There were no late changes in Canberra, with Jed Lamb (Giants) and Billie Smedts (Cats) to start the match in the green vests.
Meanwhile, in Adelaide, Sam Shaw has been brought in for his first match in nearly a year, with Daniel Talia (ill) a late withdrawal. The subs are Rory Atkins (Crows) and Josh Glenn (Suns).
Later, Richmond hosts Fremantle in the twilight clash at the MCG in one of the round’s most anticipated matches, with the Dockers hoping to retain their spot on top of the ladder.
In Saturday night’s matches, Port Adelaide will have to overcome Essendon at Etihad Stadium if they are to keep their finals chances alive for another week.
And, finally, Brent Harvey will become only the fourth player in the history of the game to play 400 matches when North Melbourne plays Brisbane at the Gabba.
Saturday’s Round 17 AFL Action (AEST):
GWS v Geelong at StarTrack Oval (1.45pm)
Adelaide v Gold Coast at the Adelaide Oval (2.10pm)
Richmond v Fremantle at the MCG (4.35pm)
Essendon v Port Adelaide at Etihad Stadium (7.20pm)
Brisbane v North Melbourne at the Gabba (7.20pm)
